definitions.definition: A state of greatly dulled or completely suspended consciousness or sensibility ; ( particularly medicine ) a chiefly mental condition marked by absence of spontaneous movement , greatly diminished responsiveness to stimulation , and usually impaired consciousness.
A state of extreme apathy or torpor resulting often from stress or shock .
